name: Bobby E. Singleton
text:
I was raised as a Baptist. My daddy was a preacher and preached at several small Baptist Churches in the Wetumpka area.

I enjoyed the small church atmosphere. When I recently moved back to Wetumpka, my first visit was to the First United Methodist Church of Wetumpka. All the people were great and welcoming.

Even though, I would not say FUMC is small, it has the small church attitude. Friendly people, and a great Minister, Matt Albritton. I was impressed with his friendly, down to earth personality. If he ever meets you once, don't be surprised if the next time he sees you he will call you by name!

resp.text: Bobby, thank you for sharing your story! It is very encouraging and we are glad to have you as part of the First United Methodist Church of Wetumpka Family!!

text: I'm not really a church goer these days, but I still have a lot of love and respect for this church.  They've always struck me as genuinely charitable.  I've been to a few different churches in the area and so many of them seem kind of greedy, using their tithes mostly for growth instead of helping others (at least not on the scale that I'd expect of a church).  Good Shepherd is always ready to help people in need, whether it's through the food pantry, storm shelter, mission trips, or hurricane-relief type trips.  United Methodists really are very accepting and kind in my opinion.  I recommend this if you're the church type that shies away from the hellfire and brimstone kind of places. name: Danii Small
text: This church definitely reminded me of home. We are new to this area so the daunting task of every move is finding a church. Finding the church, finding the kids area, getting them registered and signed in, finding our way to their classes, mazing our way back to our section of the church... Move after move, Sunday after Sunday.. It's exhausting. This time was ba bit better. Like every research I do I check the websites to see the climate of ea h church, I check reviews and I see about what kid programs they had. Whilst researching Asbury, I noticed that it was Methodist, which good or bad, we always measure up to our home church Cross point in FL. I looked at the kids services and noticed they are very active, looked at the adult services and saw a contempory one, so far so good! Getting there a parking was a breeze. Police to direct traffic and greeters to point you in the right direction. I pre-registered the kids online to make thing go more quickly, and was able to get my son where he needed to be and us to the bathrooms and seated before the singing. To top things off they had complementary coffee, tea and hot chocolate.  The contemporary service was just as expected and we enjoyed the preaching. We will be coming back to this church again this Sunday to check out the earlier service, as they only have a teen service at 0915 not the 1045 service. Not a problem though.
